📌 Project Description
This project applies machine learning techniques to predict heart failure outcomes using clinical patient data.
The main objective is to evaluate multiple classification models and address the adversarial challenge of minority class suppression by handling class imbalance using SMOTE, cross-validation, and hyperparameter tuning.

📊 Dataset
The dataset contains clinical records of heart failure patients with the following features:

Age

Anaemia

Diabetes

Ejection Fraction

Serum Creatinine

Serum Sodium

Platelets

Time

DEATH_EVENT (target variable)

Target labels:

0 = Survived

1 = Death event

🎯 Objective
To build and compare multiple machine learning models for predicting heart failure outcomes and improve performance under imbalanced data conditions.

