📈 Results
Best Model: Optimized Random Forest

AUC Score: 0.90

Improved Recall and F1-score for minority class (death events)

Cross-validation ensured robustness of the results

These findings highlight the importance of addressing class imbalance in healthcare datasets.

🏆 Conclusion
This project demonstrates that combining multiple machine learning models with resampling techniques such as SMOTE, along with cross-validation and hyperparameter tuning, significantly improves the detection of high-risk heart failure patients.
Handling minority class suppression is critical in healthcare prediction tasks and can support better clinical decision-making and patient outcomes.

